canonical_structure.name: UBX-CFG-RINV
canonical_structure.description: Contents of remote inventory. This message is deprecated in protocol versions greater than 23.01. Use UBX-CFG-VALSET, UBX-CFG-VALGET, UBX-CFG-VALDEL instead. If N is greater than 30, the excess bytes are discarded.

bits.name: dump
bits.description: Dump data at startup. Does not work if flag binary is set.

fields.name: data
fields.description: Data to store/stored in remote inventory.

issues: Uses 'explicit_count' referencing 'N', but 'N' is not defined as a field in the payload. Should use 'fill_remaining' or 'array_of' with implicit length.
Bitfield definition swapped. Standard is 'dump' at bit 0 and 'binary' at bit 1. This extraction has 'binary' at 0 and 'dump' at 1.

adjudication.reasoning: The message structure is consistent across generations: a 1-byte flag field followed by N bytes of data. The canonical flag definition puts 'dump' at bit 0 and 'binary' at bit 1, supported by 7 of the 8 sources. Extraction 8 (M8) shows a swapped bitfield, which is likely an error in reading the manual table rather than a protocol change. Extraction 6 is incomplete (missing bits). Extraction 7 uses a modeling construct ('explicit_count: N') that refers to a non-existent field variable, whereas others correctly identify the variable data nature via arrays or 'fill_remaining' semantics.
